Session 16: DoS, DDoS, Botnets, Session Hijacking
ðŸ”¹ BASIC MCQs (10)

DoS attack aims to:
A. Steal data
B. Disrupt service availability
C. Modify data
D. Bypass authentication

DDoS differs from DoS because it uses:
A. One attacker
B. Multiple distributed sources
C. Encryption
D. Firewalls

Bots are:
A. Firewalls
B. Infected machines
C. Routers
D. IDS

A botnet is:
A. Single system
B. Network of compromised machines
C. Secure network
D. VPN

Smurf attack uses:
A. TCP
B. ICMP
C. UDP
D. HTTP

SYN flooding exploits:
A. DNS
B. TCP handshake
C. ARP
D. ICMP

Session hijacking targets:
A. Availability
B. User session
C. Encryption
D. Database

Spoofing means:
A. Taking over session
B. Impersonating identity
C. Flooding traffic
D. Encrypting packets

Hijacking means:
A. Impersonation only
B. Taking control of session
C. Packet capture
D. Port scanning

Prevention of session hijacking includes:
A. Plain HTTP
B. HTTPS
C. MAC flooding
D. Open Wi-Fi

ðŸ”¸ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)

